JOHANNESBURG - A number of people have been injured and treated for smoke inhalation after a suspected gas fire at a restaurant in Rivonia, Johannesburg. Johannesburg Emergency Services spokesperson, Nana Radebe said the fire has been contained. Radebe stated eight people were transported to hospitals for medical treatment of smoke inhalation and burns, some in critical condition. "On arrival, we discovered there were blazes everywhere, the fire started at a restaurant and it is alleged that a gas bottle exploded. We are still busy with damping down and then we will begin with preliminary investigations of where the fire started and how it started," Radebe said. The fire was contained to one restaurant in the centre, however, nine businesses have been affected by the flames. A fire broke out at the Mutual Mews shopping centre in Rivonia on Saturday afternoon. Courtesy of #DStv403